The paper deals with the study of cascading failures in power systems and proposes an interaction model to simulate and mitigate such failures. The paper involves the use of probabilistic models and simulation techniques to understand the propagation patterns of cascading failures and identify key links and components that are crucial for such failures. This work involves the application of systems engineering principles and techniques to power systems, which is a typical area of research in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques to develop the interaction model, which is a typical area of research in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of network analysis and optimization techniques to identify key links and components, which is a typical area of research in the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories.
